Title: ON THE EQUIVALENCE AMONG SOME CHIRAL-BOSON THEORIES

Authors: R. Amorim and J. Barcelos-Neto

Comments: 11 pages, Latex

Journal-ref: Z.Phys. C68 (1995) 513-517

We make a comparative study of chiral-boson theories in the Florenani-Jackiw(FJ) and linear constraint formulations. A special attention is given to thecase with an improved way of implementing the linear constraint. We show thatit has the same spectrum of the FJ formulation.